      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The cyclohexadecaoctaene shown isomerizes to two different isomers, depending on reaction conditions. Explain the observed results, and indicate whether each reaction is conrotatory or disrotatory.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ1FhIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--c22ae04b533076bba86a004011bdcf34ef9d5a07/OChem_30_EC_012.jpg\" alt=\"Cyclohexadecaoctaene reacts with heat to form a tricyclic product with cis hydrogens at ortho-fused carbons. In light, there are trans hydrogens at ortho-fused carbons.\">",
